column1: Number of Child Care Providers Receiving CCDF Funds (FY 2012)
1. The source for this table is ACF-800 data for FY 2012, an unduplicated annual count.
2. This data has not been adjusted by the pooling factor (unadjusted data) because ACF-800 Data Element 6a is reported as a count of providers receiving CCDF funding.

3. Note that this table reports the number of providers (not the number of children).  A provider that serves only one child per day is counted the same as, for example, a provider serving 200 children per day.
4. At the time of publication, all States and Territories had submitted their ACF-800 data for FY 2012.

5. Virginia is not able to report the number of providers because payments are made locally and information on providers is also kept at the local level.  The State is working towards an automated system in order to report the number of providers.
